Genes: MAPK14 Expressed in AGS. No known mutations in AGS. PMID: 19629069: p38alpha and p38beta are closely related proteins that could have overlapping functions. Whereas p38alpha is highly abundant in most cell types, p38beta seems to be expressed at very low levels, and its contribution to p38 MAPK signalling is not clear. Most of the published literature on p38 MAPKs refers to p38alpha. There is much evidence to support a role for p38 as a tumour suppressor, and this function of p38 is mostly mediated by both negative regulation of cell cycle progression and the induction of apoptosis, although the induction of terminal differentiation also contributes to its tumour-suppressive function. However, p38alpha may also haveoncogenic functions that are mediated by its involvement in key processes of cancer progression, such as invasion, inflammation and angiogenesis.

PMID: 19629069: Whereas transient JNK activation was shown to promote cell survival, prolonged JNK activation mediates tumour necrosis factor-alpha (TNFalpha)-dependent apoptosis, often through distinct caspase 8 activation pathways. One pathway that has been suggested involves the E3 ubiquitin ligase ITCH, which degrades the caspase 8 inhibitor CASP8 and FADD-like apoptosis regulator (CFLAR; also known as FLIP) through JNK1 phosphorylation of ITCH.
